I"j<p>We are happy to announce the release of <a href="https://github.com/tudelft3d/Solar3Dcity">Solar3Dcity</a>, an open-source utility for the estimation of the yearly solar irradiance of buildings stored in CityGML.</p>

<p><img src="http://3dgeoinfo.bk.tudelft.nl/biljecki/github/solar3dcity/zoom-solar-nw-n-white-legend-small.png" alt="solar3dcity-header" /></p>

<p>The utility estimates the direct, diffuse and reflected solar radiation, and takes into account actual weather conditions.</p>

<p>For more information please head to the <a href="https://github.com/tudelft3d/Solar3Dcity">Github repository</a>.</p>
